==English==
===Noun===
'''schema''' (''plural:'' '''schemata''')
#an outline or image universally applicable to a general conception, under which it is likely to be presented to the mind.
#{{computing}} A formal description of the structure of a [[database]]: the names of the [[table]]s, the names of the [[column]]s of each table, and the [[type]] and other attributes of each column.  (And similarly for the descriptive information of other database-like structures, such as [[XML]] files.)
